results.name: Decimal expansion of e^(-1/2).
comment: For x = e^(-1/2), the largest prime factor of a random integer n is equally likely to be above or below n^x. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, May 25 2009
formula: Equals Sum_{k>=0} (-1)^k/(2^k * k!) = Sum_{k>=0} (-1)^k/A000165(k). - _Amiram Eldar_, Aug 15 2020
results.author: _Mohammad K. Azarian_, Apr 22 2004
